						<div class="postbody">^^^ well-put. Problem is, of course, that submappers favor lumping (+submapper assignment), and iNES backwards-compatibility favors splitting (â€¦sort of. Some mappers are allocated in this spirit, others are lumped, like MIMIC-1), and NES2.0 unifies these featuresâ€¦<br /><br />iNES header does not have a configuration meaning &quot;one-screen mirroring&quot;â€¦and the Quattro games aren't 1s, either.<br /><br /><span style="font-size: 75%; line-height: normal">I should really get back to making the submappers for PP.</span></div>

