			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The 2A03 is an NMOS device, which will sink current driving the data lines low. When two NMOS devices face contention, typically the result looks like a logical AND, so in this case, selecting Bank $01 and writing to $1C00C (containing $02) could result in Bank 0 being the result.<br /><br />I expect a typical flash rom (29F* series), a 27C* EPROM, or another ROM behind a level-translating buffer to be a CMOS device, driving data lines high and low. In this case, I would expect $02 to win.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
