				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As I see it, games tend to fall into three categories :<br /><br />Requires Bus Conflicts (bitwise AND of CPU value and ROM value) to function properly :<br />Cybernoid<br /><br />Board's Hardware ensures that the ROM's value prevails over the CPU's value :<br />Death Race (bit 0 only)<br /><br />Requires CPU's value to prevail over the ROM's value :<br />Donkey Kong Official Edition/Pie Factory (Nintendo's Official Hack)<br />Colorful Dragon (Sachen) - What about Tagin Dragon from Bunch Games?<br />Dreamworld Pogie (Codemasters, unfixed)<br /><br />What else exists?  These were the only games I could find.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nerdlypleasures.blogspot.com/" class="postlink">Nerdly Pleasures - My Vintage Video Game &amp; Computing Blog</a></div>
